---
source: tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs
assertion: ee.query.v1 temporal query-file filters apply time windows and validity posture without unsupported sentinels
schema:
  query_file: ee.query.v1
  filters: ee.query.filters.temporal.v1
contracts:
  - time.after filters candidates by created_at lower bounds
  - time.before accepts open-ended future windows and preserves deterministic ordering
  - asOf provides point-in-time behavior for query-file execution
  - temporalValidity strict/relaxed/ignore postures are parsed and applied explicitly
  - invalid timestamps retain stable timestamp validation errors
  - temporal filtering reports explainable degradation where derived data is unavailable
evidence:
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_time_after_filters_created_at
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_time_before_accepts_open_ended_future_window
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_as_of_future_snapshot_succeeds
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_temporal_validity_strict_succeeds
  - src/cli/mod.rs::temporal_filters_from_document
  - eidetic_engine_cli-lvd4
